==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Platen
<hw>Plat"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>platine</ets>, fr. <ets>plat</ets> flat. See <er>Plate</er>, and
cf. <er>Platin</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
part of a printing press which presses the paper against the type and by
which the impression is made.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Hence, an
analogous part of a typewriter, on which the paper rests to receive an
impression.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The movable table of a machine tool,
as a planer, on which the work is fastened, and presented to the action
of the tool; -- also called <altname>table</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plater</ent>⟦br⟧
